messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I'm walking in the field. I don't know where I am.
You're walking in a field? Okay, I need you to just stop. I'm going to try to find you on my screen.
Did you go in the ditch?
Yes, then we started walking.
We thought it was close enough.
Okay, can you go back to your vehicle?
I can't. I don't know where it is.
You don't know where it is? Okay. I want you to just stay on the line with me. It looks like I can find you.
What road were you driving on?
We were coming up this hour.
Okay, one second. I'm still online with you, okay?
Hello?
Okay, I'm still online with you. How many people are with you?
Me and one other person.
Okay. Do you remember which way you were walking, or did you totally get turned around?
No, I don't know.
Okay, what I want you to do is stay on the line. I'm trying to pull you up on the map right now to see if I can find a location showing which way you are walking.
Can you start walking? Do you know which way West is?
I don't know. I don't.
Do you know where Prairie Road is?
I don't know.
Okay, I want you to start walking. You're going to have to walk one way or the other, and then I'll be able to tell you which way to go.
Do you have enough clothing on?
No, I came from a wedding. I don't have much.
Okay, I'm going to page out some people to help find you.
I want you to stay on the line with me, okay?
I'm crying. Okay?
I don't know, I'll lose it if I stay here.
I can't get over.
Please hold.
Hello?
Hello?
Hello?
Hello?
